## TYPOGRAPHY

Three font roles. They never substitute each other.

```
DISPLAY   Playfair Display, serif, weight 700
          → App name, hero title, onboarding headline
          → letter-spacing: -0.02em

HEADING   DM Serif Display, serif, weight 400
          → Section titles, screen titles, card titles
          → letter-spacing: -0.01em

BODY      DM Sans, sans-serif, weight 400 / 500 / 600
          → Everything else: description, button, label, meta
          → letter-spacing: 0
```

### Size Scale
```
2xs   11px  lh 1.4    badge, timestamp
xs    13px  lh 1.5    author name, meta, chip label
sm    15px  lh 1.6    body text, description
md    17px  lh 1.4    card title
lg    20px  lh 1.3    section title
xl    24px  lh 1.2    screen title
2xl   30px  lh 1.1    hero text
3xl   38px  lh 1.0    display / app name
```

**Rule:** Never use more than 3 different sizes on one screen. Build hierarchy with color and weight, not size jumps.

**Rule:** Numbers and stats (14 books, 55%, 17-day streak) always use HEADING font at large size. Never body font.

**Rule:** Button labels are always sentence case or Title Case. Never ALL CAPS.

**Rule:** Body text is never bold. Use color difference for emphasis, not weight.

---

## SPACING

4px grid. Never go outside this grid anywhere.

```
1  →   4px
2  →   8px
3  →  12px
4  →  16px
5  →  20px
6  →  24px
8  →  32px
10 →  40px
12 →  48px
16 →  64px
```

- Horizontal screen edge padding: always **20px**
- Vertical gap between sections: **28px**
- Card inner padding: **16px**

---

## BORDER RADIUS

```
xs      4px     small inline tag
sm      8px     input field, small element
md     12px     small card
lg     16px     standard card
xl     20px     large card
2xl    24px     modal, bottom sheet, drawer
full  9999px    pill button, avatar, badge, progress bar
book    8px     book cover — this token never changes
```

---

## SHADOWS

```
sm    0 2px  8px  rgba(0,0,0,0.15)   card
md    0 4px  16px rgba(0,0,0,0.25)   book cover, elevated card
lg    0 8px  32px rgba(0,0,0,0.40)   modal, bottom sheet
```

- In dark mode: use shadows freely
- In light mode: prefer border over shadow. Do not stack both.

---

## ICONS

```
Style       outlined, stroke-width 1.5–2px, no fill
Sizes       20px nav bar   22px action   24px header
Color       passive → text.muted     active → accent.warm
Library     lucide-react or phosphor-icons
```

---

## IMAGES

### Book Cover
```
Aspect ratio   2:3 (width:height) — never change this
Object-fit     cover
Border radius  8px (book token)
Shadow         md
Missing cover  background.layer + centered book icon
```

### Avatar
```
Small    32px   border-radius full
Medium   44px   border-radius full
Large    64px   border-radius full
Featured border: 2px solid accent.warm
```

### Hero / Banner Image
```
Aspect ratio   16:9 or 3:2
Overlay        linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent 40%, rgba(0,0,0,0.85))
               text always sits on top of the gradient, never on the raw image
```

---

## MOTION

```
Fast      150ms ease-out           button tap, chip select
Normal    250ms ease-in-out        card, panel open/close
Page      350ms ease-in-out        screen transition

Easing    cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)

Bottom sheet    translateY(100%) → translateY(0), 300ms
Card press      scale(0.97), 150ms
Progress fill   width 400ms ease
```

---

## HUMAN TOUCH RULES

These rules are the difference between AI output and hand-crafted UI. Apply them on every screen.

### Asymmetry & Breathing Room
- Sections do not need to be the same height. Let content dictate.
- One featured item can be full-width while others sit in a small grid below.
- Generous negative space in one area balances density in another.

### Accent Color Economy
- accent.warm appears maximum 2–3 times per screen.
- Never spread it across every icon, button, and label at once.
- When overused, it loses all meaning. Restraint makes it powerful.

### Gradient Discipline
- Gradients go from transparent to color, not from color to color.
- Overlay gradients exist for readability only — not decoration.
- A very subtle noise texture on backgrounds (opacity 0.03–0.06) adds realism. Use it.

### Typography Confidence
- When using DISPLAY font, go big. Be bold. Do not shrink it to play safe.
- Tracking (letter-spacing) on display text should be tight, not open.
- Card titles that exceed 2 lines get line-clamp. Never let them overflow into a third line.

### Layer Contrast
- Background layers should shift subtly, not abruptly.
- The difference between background.base and background.layer should be visible but calm.
- Never jump from very dark to white in adjacent elements.

---

## ACCESSIBILITY (non-negotiable)

```
Touch target minimum    44 × 44px
Contrast normal text    4.5 : 1
Contrast large text     3.0 : 1
Minimum font size       11px
Focus indicator         2px solid accent.warm, offset 3px
```

---

## NEVER DO

```
✗  Use Inter, Roboto, or Arial — they read as generic
✗  Purple gradient on white background — it is a cliché
✗  Square aspect ratio for book covers
✗  More than 4 color tones on one screen
✗  ALL CAPS button labels
✗  Shadow in light mode alongside border — pick one
✗  Scatter accent color across every interactive element
✗  Fixed-height cards — let content define height
✗  Bold body text — use color for emphasis instead
✗  Raw hex values in component code — use tokens
```
